.\" Manpage for wxpegged.
.\" Translated from the CHM help book (wxpeggedchm/*.htm).
.TH WXPEGGED 6 "April 2026" "wxpegged 1.0" "Games"
.SH NAME
wxpegged \- a peg-solitaire game (wxWidgets port of Pegged)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B wxpegged
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B wxpegged
is a portable wxWidgets port of the Microsoft Entertainment Pack game
\fBPegged\fR (also known as "Jump" or "Peg Solitaire"). It is a game of
logic with origins dating back to the 19th Century, reputedly invented
by a prisoner of the Bastille and popular throughout Europe in the
1800s, where it was played by moving pegs in a wooden board.
.PP
The playing area is a plus-shaped grid of holes. At the start of a game
the holes contain a configuration of pegs. A peg is moved by jumping it
across an adjacent peg into the open hole on the other side. Only
horizontal and vertical jumps are allowed; diagonal jumps are illegal.
The jumped peg is automatically removed from the board.
.PP
The object of the game is to jump pegs so that only one remains.
Finishing with the last peg in the center of the board is considered
the "coolest" result, but any finish with a single peg left is a win.
.SH PLAYING THE GAME
.TP
.B Selecting a board type
Choose
.BR Cross ,
.BR Plus ,
.BR Fireplace ,
.BR "Up Arrow" ,
.BR Pyramid ,
.BR Diamond ,
or
.B Solitaire
from the
.B Options
menu. Each board presents a different starting peg configuration of
increasing difficulty.
.TP
.B Starting a new game
Choose
.B New
from the
.B Game
menu, or press
.BR F2 .
.TP
.B Jumping a peg
Press the left mouse button on a peg, drag it across an adjacent peg,
and release it on the empty hole on the far side. If the move is legal
the jumped peg is removed; otherwise the dragged peg snaps back.
.SH RULES OF THE GAME
.IP 1. 3
The playing area is a plus-shaped grid of holes. At the beginning of
each game a particular peg configuration is placed in the area.
.IP 2. 3
A peg is removed by jumping another peg over it. Only certain jumps
are legal: jumps must be strictly horizontal or vertical, one peg at a
time, over an occupied hole into an empty hole directly on the other
side.
.IP 3. 3
The game is over when no legal jumps remain. If only one peg is left
on the board, you win.
.SH GAME MENU COMMANDS
.TP
.B New
Starts a new game of
.BR wxpegged .
Can be invoked at any time, including mid-game; keyboard shortcut
.BR F2 .
.TP
.B Backup
Backs up (undoes) one jump. You can continue to back up until the
initial peg configuration is reached. Keyboard shortcut
.B Ctrl+Z
(or
.BR Backspace ).
.TP
.B Exit
Exits
.BR wxpegged .
Can be invoked at any time, including mid-game.
.SH OPTIONS MENU COMMANDS
The Options menu selects the initial configuration of the pegs. Pick
one of:
.BR Cross ", " Plus ", " Fireplace ", " "Up Arrow" ", " Pyramid ", "
.BR Diamond ", or " Solitaire .
Each presents a distinct challenge; the last peg's winning position is
the center hole.
.SH HELP MENU COMMANDS
.TP
.B How to Play
Opens this help. On Linux the man page is displayed; on Windows the
bundled \fIwxpegged.chm\fR is opened; on macOS the bundled
\fIPegged.help\fR book is shown. Keyboard shortcut
.BR F1 .
.TP
.B About Pegged...
Shows the About dialog with version and copyright information.
.SH STRATEGY AND HINTS
Start with the simplest puzzle,
.BR Cross ,
then solve each of the other puzzles in the Options menu from top to
bottom. The puzzles get progressively harder, but each one provides
insights into how the hardest puzzle,
.BR Solitaire ,
may be solved. Working back from the desired final-peg position is
often useful: a jump played forwards from (a) over (b) into (c) is the
mirror of one played backwards from (c) over (b) into (a).
